ce:section.ce:para:
Synthesized materials have been extensively characterized using Fourier transform infrared (FTIR) spectroscopy using a KBr disc. FTIR spectroscopy was used to confirm the synthesis of GQD-bTiO2 NF composites (Fig. 1
                        ). The FTIR spectrum of bTiO2 NFs has peaks at 790 and 1380 cm−1 (attributed to the bending mode of surface adsorbed water on the bTiO2 
                        [25]) whereas GQDs have peaks at 1065, 1608, and 2902 cm−1. All these peaks are conserved in the FTIR spectra of the composites.
